title: Senator Faisal pays tribute GB for rejecting anti-state rhetoric
content:
ISLAMABAD, Nov 15 (APP): Senator Faisal Javed Khan on Sunday paid tribute to the people who have rejected the anti-state rhetoric in Gilgit Baltistan election.
In a twitter message, he said that “salute the spirit of Pakistanis – the whole nation stands with the state and rejected those who work against it”, adding that this election is a lesson for Pakistan Democratic Movement (PDM).
گلگت بلتستان کی عوام کو خراج تحسین جنہوں نے ریاست مخالف بیانیہ مسترد کر دیا ہے – پوری قوم ریاست کے ساتھ کھڑی ہے اور اس کے خلاف کام کرنے والوں کو رجیکٹ کر چکی ہے-یہ الیکشن پی ڈی ایم کے لیے سبق آموز ہے شکریہ گلگت بلتستان #ہو_گئی_انصاف_کی_جیت
— Faisal Javed Khan (@FaisalJavedKhan) November 15, 2020
Congratulating people of Gilgit Baltistan, he said that this victory, is the victory of the people of GB.
He further said that this victory is the victory of justice and war against corruption, adding that this victory is against those who have been looting country from decades.
